    "body": "I also made a simpler test which exclude state transition stuff:\r\n\r\n```\r\nit.only(\"test hashTreeRoot\", async function () {\r\n    let start = Date.now();\r\n    const state = generateState();\r\n    console.log('@@@ generateState took ', Date.now() - start);\r\n    start = Date.now();\r\n    hashTreeRoot(\r\n      state,\r\n      config.types.BeaconState\r\n    );\r\n    console.log('@@@ hashTreeRoot took ', Date.now() - start);\r\n  });\r\n```\r\nThe result is\r\n```\r\n@@@ generateState took  33\r\n@@@ hashTreeRoot took  833\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt means that this performance issue is nothing related to state .transition, it's merely hashTreeRoot performance.",
